<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <title>{{ title }}</title>
    <link rel='stylesheet' href='/stylesheets/style.css' />
    <script src='/js/adminFunctions.js'></script>
  </head>
  <body>
  <div id="adminwrap">
    <div id="adminhead">
      <h2>Simulation Setup</h2>
    </div>
    <div id="adminmain">
      <div id="adminmaindisplay">
        <h3>Options Will Display Here.<br />
        We can set it up so the Simulation Customize one is default</h3>
        <p>I slapped this together as a proof of concept. With this we can see how to pull in users and add them dynamically using moustache/hogan/whatever you call it.<br />
        It also shows how we can send a POST request to create and 'store' a room in an in-memory DB.<br />
        We also get some insight on some basic UI shit. Obviously all of this is well up for discussion.<br />
        <br />
        See:<ul>
        <li>views/sc-admin.hjs</li>
        <li>public/js/adminFunctions.js (this is definitely going out the window but it's a good example)</li>
        <li>db.js</li>
        <li>routes/scadmin.js (this one shows Hogan in action a little bit)</li>
        </ul>
        </p>
      </div>
      <div id="adminmainfooter">
        <form role="form" method="POST" action="/sc-admin/addroom">
          <input type="text" class="form" id="room" name="room" placeholder="Room Name" />
          <button type="submit">Accept and Create Room</button>
          <div><p>{{ roomname }}</p></div>
        </form>
        <ul>
        <!-- This is pretty important. You have to use three {'s to render as HTML -->
        <!-- Otherwise it's just text. -->
        {{{ userlist }}}
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div id="adminside">
      <ul id="simoptions" class="buttonlist">
        <li id="option1" class="buttonitem" onclick="teamSelection()">Team Selection</li>
        <li id="option2" class="buttonitem" onclick="option2()">Option2</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
  </body>
</html>
